<subSubSection pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="122.[151,1437,1037,1952]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1694,1720]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name refers to the shining posterior half of female sternite 7 which is diagnostic for this species (Lat. 
<emphasis box="[397,467,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">nitens</emphasis>
: shining, glittering).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="122.[151,1437,1037,1952]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
