</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="122.[151,1437,1037,1952]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,1848,1874]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Discussion</emphasis>
. The female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Buck &amp; Marshall, 2009" authorityName="Buck &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2009" box="[546,741,1849,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Leptocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="posteronitens" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[546,741,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">L. posteronitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[756,811,1849,1875]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is easily recognisable by its large, shining black posteromedial projection of sternite 7. Otherwise it is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Buck &amp; Marshall, 2009" authorityName="Buck &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2009" box="[993,1110,1888,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Leptocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapanti" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[993,1110,1888,1913]" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">L. tapanti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1120,1175,1888,1914]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1253,1384,1888,1914]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,248,1926,1952]" name="Panama" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Panama</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
